description.narrative: In 2019, (i) 598 under 5 Children were admitted for treatment for Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM) in the first semester; (ii) 61% of coverage was achieved in a first round of Vitamin A supplementation conducted in routine activity using community health workers agents; (iii) 10790 out of 10964 (98%) school age children received deworming tablets in the 47 child-friendly schools within five regions (iv) 62 health technicians were trained to promote the ten steps for the successful breastfeeding in 3 selected health structure and (v) the second National Nutrition SMART survey was conducted. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
